    • Method Detail

      • $

        @NotNull
public static org.openqa.selenium.WebElement $(@NotNull
                                                        java.util.List<? extends org.openqa.selenium.SearchContext> $receiver,
                                                        @NotNull
                                                        java.lang.String selector,
                                                        int index)

        Find the nth element that can be located within the current context by the given CSS selector.

        This is an alternative to the find method.

        // Given the Kotlin's website index page URL
val indexPageUrl = "https://kotlinlang.org/"

Browser.drive(driverFactory) {
    // When I visit such URL
    to(indexPageUrl)

    // Then I should get the different platforms Kotlin works on, in alphabetical order
    assertEquals(
        `$`("a.works-on-item").`$`(".works-on-text", 1, 2, 0, 3).map { it.text.trim() },
        listOf("Android", "Browser", "JVM", "Native"))

    // And I should get the Try-Kotlin section's description
    assertEquals(
        `$`(".global-layout").`$`(".section-description", 0).text.replace("(?m)\\s+".toRegex(), " "),
        "Explore Kotlin code samples and solve problems directly in the browser Try online")

    // And I should get the second and third stay-in-touch methods
    assertEquals(
        `$`(".links-list li a").`$`("span:nth-of-type(2)", 1..2).map { it.text },
        listOf("Community", "Twitter"))
}

        Parameters:
        selector - the CSS selector to be used for locating the element.
        index - the index of the element to be returned.
        Returns:
        The nth matching element within the current context.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IndexOutOfBoundsException - for an illegal index value.

        Find all the elements that can be located by the given CSS selector within the current context, restricted by the specified range.

        This is an alternative to the find method.

val indexPageUrl = "https://kotlinlang.org/"

Browser.drive(driverFactory) {
    // When I visit such URL
    to(indexPageUrl)

    // Then I should get the different platforms Kotlin works on, in alphabetical order

        `$`("a.works-on-item").`$`(".works-on-text", 1, 2, 0, 3).map { it.text.trim() },

    // And I should get the Try-Kotlin section's description

        `$`(".global-layout").`$`(".section-description", 0).text.replace("(?m)\\s+".toRegex(), " "),
        "Explore Kotlin code samples and solve problems directly in the browser Try online")

    // And I should get the second and third stay-in-touch methods
    assertEquals(
        `$`(".links-list li a").`$`("span:nth-of-type(2)", 1..2).map { it.text },
        listOf("Community", "Twitter"))
}

        Parameters:
        selector - the CSS selector to be used for locating the elements.
        range - specify the indices of the elements to be returned.
        Returns:
        The matching elements within the current context, restricted by the specified range.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IndexOutOfBoundsException - for illegal index values within the range.

        @NotNull
public static java.util.List<org.openqa.selenium.WebElement> $(@NotNull

        Find all the elements that can be located by the given CSS selector within the current context, restricted by the specified indices. (If no index is provided, then all matching elements will be returned.)

        This is an alternative to the find method.

        // Given the Kotlin's website index page URL
val indexPageUrl = "https://kotlinlang.org/"

Browser.drive(driverFactory) {
    // When I visit such URL
    to(indexPageUrl)

    // Then I should get the different platforms Kotlin works on, in alphabetical order
    assertEquals(
        `$`("a.works-on-item").`$`(".works-on-text", 1, 2, 0, 3).map { it.text.trim() },
        listOf("Android", "Browser", "JVM", "Native"))

    // And I should get the Try-Kotlin section's description
    assertEquals(
        `$`(".global-layout").`$`(".section-description", 0).text.replace("(?m)\\s+".toRegex(), " "),
        "Explore Kotlin code samples and solve problems directly in the browser Try online")

    // And I should get the second and third stay-in-touch methods
    assertEquals(
        `$`(".links-list li a").`$`("span:nth-of-type(2)", 1..2).map { it.text },
        listOf("Community", "Twitter"))
}

        Parameters:
        selector - the CSS selector to be used for locating the elements.
        indices - the indices of the elements to be returned.
        Returns:
        The matching elements within the current context restricted by the specified indices. (Or all matching elements if no index is provided.)
        Throws:
        java.lang.IndexOutOfBoundsException - for illegal index values.
